The rand steadied against the dollar early on Wednesday, holding near a five-week high hit in the previous session as rising hopes of a $1.9 trillion stimulus programme in the United States elevated risk demand. At 0700 GMT, the rand traded at R14.73 against the US dollar, compared to a previous close of R14.74 – its strongest level since January 5. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
